      • getInputOption

        public int getInputOption(java.lang.String options)
        Gets input from user. Input must be an integer. If input is not an integer, or if the input is not one of the listed options, the user will be prompted until valid input is entered.
        Parameters:
        options - string of options passed in by a state class
        Returns:
        returns the option requested from the user

      • getInputString

        public java.lang.String getInputString()
        getInputString prompts the user for field names such as their first name, department, building, etc. These field names will be processed as strings as opposed to getInputOption which takes in an integer from the user
        Returns:
        getInputString returns the field name entered, which will be written out into its respective location
